    "created_at": "2014-06-17T08:13:31Z",
    "updated_at": "2014-06-17T08:13:31Z",
    "body": "There is no shared context in atom-shell, if you want to share an object between windows you can store the object in browser process and use `remote` module to access it in renderer:\n\n``` javascript\n// In main.js of browser process\nglobal.sharedObject = {};\n```\n\n``` javascript\n// js in 1.html\nrequire('remote').getGlobal('sharedObject').someProperty = 'some value';\n```\n\n``` javascript\n// js in 2.html\nconsole.log(require('remote').getGlobal('sharedObject').someProperty);\n```\n\nYou can also use `localStorage` to store shared data.\n"
  },
